# Shadcn UI Component Guidelines

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements and components.

## üö® CRITICAL RULES - NO EXCEPTIONS

### ONLY shadcn/ui Components
**ABSOLUTELY NO custom UI components should be created in this project.**

- ‚ùå **NEVER** create custom buttons, inputs, cards, dialogs, or any UI elements from scratch
- ‚ùå **NEVER** write custom styled components when a shadcn/ui equivalent exists
- ‚ùå **NEVER** use plain HTML elements like `<button>`, `<input>`, `<dialog>` for UI
- ‚úÖ **ALWAYS** use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`
- ‚úÖ **ALWAYS** install missing shadcn/ui components rather than creating custom ones

**If you need a UI element:**
1. First, check if shadcn/ui has it: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components
2. Install it with `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`
3. Use the installed component from `@/components/ui/`

