## Clerk Authentication Integration

**MANDATORY: Clerk must use shadcn/ui components with modals**

### Sign In / Sign Up Buttons
- ‚úÖ **ALWAYS** use shadcn/ui `Button` component for Clerk sign-in/sign-up triggers
- ‚ùå **NEVER** use Clerk's default `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` components
- ‚ùå **NEVER** use separate sign-in/sign-up pages (use modals instead)

### Required Components
Install these shadcn/ui components for Clerk integration:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
```

### Implementation Example
```tsx
"use client";

import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import {
  Dialog,
  DialogContent,
  DialogDescription,
  DialogHeader,
  DialogTitle,
  DialogTrigger,
} from "@/components/ui/dialog";
import { SignIn, SignUp } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export function AuthButtons() {
  return (
    <div className="flex gap-4">
      {/* Sign In Modal */}
      <Dialog>
        <DialogTrigger asChild>
          <Button variant="outline">Sign In</Button>
        </DialogTrigger>
        <DialogContent>
          <DialogHeader>
            <DialogTitle>Sign In</DialogTitle>
            <DialogDescription>
              Sign in to your account to continue
            </DialogDescription>
          </DialogHeader>
          <SignIn routing="hash" />
        </DialogContent>
      </Dialog>

      {/* Sign Up Modal */}
      <Dialog>
        <DialogTrigger asChild>
          <Button>Sign Up</Button>
        </DialogTrigger>
        <DialogContent>
          <DialogHeader>
            <DialogTitle>Create Account</DialogTitle>
            <DialogDescription>
              Create a new account to get started
            </DialogDescription>
          </DialogHeader>
          <SignUp routing="hash" />
        </DialogContent>
      </Dialog>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Key Points for Clerk Integration:**
- Use `routing="hash"` on `<SignIn>` and `<SignUp>` components for modal usage
- Wrap shadcn/ui Dialog triggers with `asChild` prop
- Use shadcn/ui Button variants for different styles (`outline`, `default`, `ghost`, etc.)
- Keep authentication UI in modals, not separate pages

